external_knowledge:
- 'crown jewels of anime' refers to the most popular anime series; 
- 'most treasured titles' refers to the titles of the anime series with the highest watchlist and review counts; 
- 'average captivation level' refers to the average rating of the anime series; 
- 'number of critiques they have received' refers to the review count of the anime series; 
- 'the number of times they have been added to a watchlist' refers to the watchlist count of the anime series.

Anime series refer to Japanese animated productions; 
The average rating and review rating are likely based on a scale of 1 to 5, where 1 is the lowest rating and 5 is the highest;
The watchlist status count refers to the number of users who have added the anime series to their watchlists with a specific status (e.g., "Watched", "Dropped", "Want to Watch");
The genre names are concatenated in a single string, separated by commas.

sql:
SELECT series_id
   FROM anime_series_genres
   WHERE genre_id = 0;

SELECT title, avg_rating, episode_count
FROM anime_series
WHERE series_id = 1;
